                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>Papers, 1901-1935.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>Correspondence, scrapbook, and photographs.  Letters are from Gates' father, John T. Brush, and Harry S. New; one concerns Harry M. Daugherty in the wake of the Teapot Dome Scandal.  The scrapbook contains memorabilia of her social life and activities in the local and national Junior League.  Photographs are of the Brush family. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Indiana Historical Society Library</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>
